#: ../../manual/render/lighting/lamps/point.rst:12
msgid ""
"The *Point* lamp is an omni-directional point of light, that is, a point radiating the same amount of "
"light in all directions. It's visualized by a plain, circled dot. Being a point light source, the "
"direction of the light hitting an object's surface is determined by the line joining the lamp and the "
"point on the surface of the object itself. It can be used as simple model of e.g. a light bulb."
msgstr ""
"点光灯是一个全方位的光，也就是说，在所有方向上发射相同数量的光。它由一个简单的带圆圈的点表示。作为点光源，"
"光线照射物体表面的方向由连接灯的线和物体表面上的点本身决定。它可以用作简单的模型，例如灯泡。"

#: ../../manual/render/lighting/lamps/point.rst:19
msgid ""
"Light intensity/energy decays based on (among other variables) distance from the *Point* lamp to the "
"object. In other words, surfaces that are further away are rendered darker."
msgstr "光的强度/能量基于（除了其他变量）从 *点光* 灯到物体的距离而衰减。换句话说，更远的表面将变得更暗。"

